The public passenger transport sector is taking a further hit from COVID19. PUTCO says its retrenching retrenching 214 workers. #eNCA​ speaks to Putco's Labour Relations Executive, Pride Anozie. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The public passenger transport sector is taking a further hit from COVID19. Bus company Putco says its retrenching 214 workers. READ: Greyhound, Citiliner closing shop after 37 years Putco has a fleet of 1,400 buses and transports about 210,000 passengers daily. On Wednesday, luxury liner Greyhound announced it will be discontinuing services from the middle of the month. Bus company Putco is set to retrench 214 employees due to financial distress caused by COVID-19. #DStv403​ #eNCA